18 SECTION 2.
19 Article VII, Section III of the Constitution is amended by adding a new paragraph at the end
20 thereof to read as follows:
21 "Paragraph V. Sales or income tax credit or exemption. On or after January 1, 2027, no
22 bill proposing any sales or income tax credit or sales or income tax exemption shall become
23 law unless it receives a two-thirds' vote of the members elected to each house of the
24 General Assembly."
25 SECTION 3.
26 The above proposed amendment to the Constitution shall be published and submitted as
27 provided in Article X, Section I, Paragraph II of the Constitution. The ballot submitting the
28 above proposed amendment shall have written or printed thereon the following:
29 "( ) YES Shall the Constitution of Georgia be amended so as to require a two-thirds'
30 vote of the General Assembly for any special interest sales or income tax
31 ( ) NO credit or special interest sales or income tax exemption to become law?"
32 All persons desiring to vote in favor of ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "Yes."
33 All persons desiring to vote against ratifying the proposed amendment shall vote "No." If
34 such amendment shall be ratified as provided in said Paragraph of the Constitution, it shall
35 become a part of the Constitution of this state.
